<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4370] hsha server may stop responding and will not close selectors</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4370</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Cassandra launches several threads to listen on selectors. There can be CancelledKeyException and cassandra will log &quot;Unexpected exception&quot;. In that case there two problems:&lt;br/&gt;
1) listener thread will be closed and cassandra will stop after all listener threads will stop.&lt;br/&gt;
2) selector will be not closed&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12595782">CASSANDRA-4370</key>
            <summary>hsha server may stop responding and will not close selectors</summary>
