                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13400440" author="kvaster" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 12:21:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13400653" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 16:57:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1) I am wondering when will we get the CancelledKeyException? &lt;br/&gt;
We might get it when the client decides to exit out, isn&apos;t it safe to ignore it (may ignore the log as well) and let the following code deal with it?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;                    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!key.isValid())
                    {
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; invalid cleanup.
&lt;/span&gt;                        cleanupSelectionkey(key);
                        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;continue&lt;/span&gt;;
                    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) Why should we close the selector when one of the key is invalid?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13400966" author="kvaster" created="Mon, 25 Jun 2012 22:14:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;1) This code is not enough. Even if key is valid in that expression, it may be invalid in next statement - I was able to reproduce it on my boxes with cassandra 1.1.1.&lt;br/&gt;
2) We should not close selector at all until server shutdown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13401096" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Tue, 26 Jun 2012 01:42:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, Committed to 1.1 and trunk, (Misread the patch earlier)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
